Interface DPAPIUtil.Crypt32Ext

All Superinterfaces:
com.sun.jna.AltCallingConvention, com.sun.jna.platform.win32.Crypt32, com.sun.jna.Library, com.sun.jna.win32.StdCall, com.sun.jna.win32.StdCallLibrary
Enclosing class:
DPAPIUtil
public static interface DPAPIUtil.Crypt32Ext extends com.sun.jna.platform.win32.Crypt32
The Crypt32Ext interface extends the Crypt32 interface from JNA to load the native Crypt32 library and define the required DPAPI methods.

  • Method Details

    • CryptProtectData

      boolean CryptProtectData(com.sun.jna.platform.win32.WinCrypt.DATA_BLOB pDataIn, String szDataDescr, com.sun.jna.platform.win32.WinCrypt.DATA_BLOB pOptionalEntropy, com.sun.jna.Pointer pvReserved, com.sun.jna.Pointer pPromptStruct, int dwFlags, com.sun.jna.platform.win32.WinCrypt.DATA_BLOB pDataOut)
      Encrypts the data in a DATA_BLOB structure.
      Parameters:
      pDataIn - The DATA_BLOB structure that contains the plaintext data to be encrypted.
      szDataDescr - A description string. This parameter can be null.
      pOptionalEntropy - A DATA_BLOB structure that contains a password or other additional entropy used to encrypt the data. This parameter can be null.
      pvReserved - Reserved for future use and must be null.
      pPromptStruct - A pointer to a CRYPTPROTECT_PROMPTSTRUCT structure that provides information about where and when prompts are to be displayed. This parameter can be null.
      dwFlags - A set of bit flags that indicate options for encryption.
      pDataOut - The DATA_BLOB structure that receives the encrypted data.
      Returns:
      Returns true if the function succeeds, false otherwise.

    • CryptUnprotectData

      boolean CryptUnprotectData(com.sun.jna.platform.win32.WinCrypt.DATA_BLOB pDataIn, com.sun.jna.ptr.PointerByReference szDataDescr, com.sun.jna.platform.win32.WinCrypt.DATA_BLOB pOptionalEntropy, com.sun.jna.Pointer pvReserved, com.sun.jna.Pointer pPromptStruct, int dwFlags, com.sun.jna.platform.win32.WinCrypt.DATA_BLOB pDataOut)
      Decrypts the data in a DATA_BLOB structure.
      Parameters:
      pDataIn - The DATA_BLOB structure that contains the encrypted data.
      szDataDescr - A pointer to a string that receives a description of the data. This parameter can be null.
      pOptionalEntropy - A DATA_BLOB structure that contains a password or other additional entropy used to encrypt the data. This parameter can be null.
      pvReserved - Reserved for future use and must be null.
      pPromptStruct - A pointer to a CRYPTPROTECT_PROMPTSTRUCT structure that provides information about where and when prompts are to be displayed. This parameter can be null.
      dwFlags - A set of bit flags that indicate options for decryption.
      pDataOut - The DATA_BLOB structure that receives the decrypted data.
      Returns:
      Returns true if the function succeeds, false otherwise.
